{
  "version": 3,
  "_comment": "Bootstrap fleet policies (Keel M2, extended for M5 wave-1 connectors). Installed to ~/.assistant/policies/policies.json on first triage run when no live file exists. On later runs a version bump here ADDs any rule ids missing from the installed file (never overwrites or removes user rules) and ledgers the upgrade. Ordered, first-match-wins. Every id has a fixture in evals/policy/<id>/ enforced by tests/test_policy.py coverage. M5: github + gmail rules are now present because their producers (bin/connectors/github-notifications.py, bin/connectors/gmail.py) exist and their WorldEvent kinds are known (github kind = notification reason; gmail kind = mechanical newsletter|direct|message from Gmail's own labels/headers) — the M2-era data-hiding hazard (guessing a schema before the producer existed) no longer applies. No rule uses the `auto` lane (the triage lane map structurally cannot emit auto; auto is confirmed-policy-only). Mutations to the LIVE file go through confirmed `policy` proposals, not hand edits.",
  "policies": [
